<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="686" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d686">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram in cipher.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-15"><hi rend="italic">January 15,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>[Mr. Choate reports that the question of the ownership of the <hi rend="italic">Mashona’s</hi> cargo was embarrassed by the fact that
                            the British foreign office was advised that the vessel had no manifest,
                            and inquires as to the correctness of this advice.]</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>